for the melees.<br><br><br>/Pet Attack Name /Assist. This trick allows pet classes to target players from afar. Vs other casters it gives you the ability to always land the first blow even if your not smart enough to actually find and target the person. Vs melees it allows you to kill or hurt the melee without ever comming into view because you can simply target them and spam a spell till they walk into range which is more troublesome as it is very unfair to the melee.<br><br>Solution-add a new response if the person being targeted with /pet attack name is not close to the pet in question AND in sight.  The pet should say I cannot see him/her master.  In order for this not to ruin coh /invite name should be made a valid command so you can invite people from anywhere in the zone.<br><br><br>Casting through walls.  Again the melee is denied the chance to fight back.  This is not fair and is very poor design and not helped by the fact that the pet attack name assist trick exists.<br><br>Solution- Ever noticed you can't nuke an npc through a wall or ceiling? Thats because it uses code to prevent casting on npcs not in line of sight.  This same code could protect players without limiting the use of heals and buffs to los.<br><br><br>Hill bugs.  Sucks to have someone run up a hil and disapear then start nuking enough said I think.<br><br>Solution-Its a bug fix it!<br><br><br>Levitate.   2 things.  1) hovering over water and casting on people who can't hit you.  2) floating way the hell in the air where you can't be hit.<br><br>Solution- Either improve pumice or make it so you can't cast any offensive spells while levitated like scale of wolf<br><br><br>Shaman dmg shield potions.  There is absolutely nothing wrong with these being around except for the fact that they stack with druid and mage ds. This brings the druids potential dmg shield from 38 to a ridiculous 69 per hit.<br><br>Solution-Make the potions and druid/mage ds the same spell line so they wont stack.<br><br><br>Zone control.  Its very annoying to be attacked by an enemy who you killed only 5-10 minutes ago.  Even more so if your a melee and they are a caster bound in the zone.<br><br>Item loot.  Its a broken concept.  In no way does it award the better pvper.  In fact I think it tends to reward the people who use the most cheap strategies and wear the least gear to lose themselves.<br><br>Solution- remove item loot and make the penalty for death the inability to log on that char for a certain perdiod of time.  Starting with a short amount of time in the early lvls and a longer time later on.  This would be for me preferable to both exp loss and item loss.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urhainy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhainy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/31/01 6:00:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> I agree with you on most things but I don't think levi or shaman DS potions or anything like that are bugs, that's what golem wands are for. And as far as item loot, only one server has item loot and 3 don't, maybe you should move servers. Not being able to log on would frustate most people to no end. <br><br>And I'll add a bug to the list: <br><br>Charm bug. That bug where your sitting there minding your own buisness a lvl 50 in a lvl 10 zone sitting near a guard. When suddenly a large rat attacks and next thing you know the uber newbie guards are tearing you apart... and you eat a nice exp death to a lvl 14 druid.. When someone charms something and has it attack you, for some reason the guards join in even if you don't attack back. That's a horrible bug and needs to be fixed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/1/01 10:20:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> what a fantasticly short list...lemme see if I can find a longer one.<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessage?topicID=215.topic">pub13.ezboard.com/fthesaf...=215.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/1/01 10:25:36 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/1/01 3:03:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> #1 bug: melee range bug. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/2/01 12:40:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> I don't agree with removing zone pulling.<br><br>Simply put casters have many many ways of disingaging from combat without death and pure melees have none other than pulling the plug.<br><br>Divine Aura<br>Harm shield<br>Shadowstep<br>Yonder<br>Gate<br>Spirit of Cheetah<br><br>and the big one...<br><br>Running.  Due to melee range issues if poison has worn off or has been resisted its very hard to finish anyone who wants to run.<br><br>Fact is a classes pvp success isn't just determined by the numbers of wins and losses but the extent of those wins and losses.  If you win 19 out of 20 fights but got not one kill and during the one loss you died and had your breastplate looted you not only lost but lost big time.<br><br>It is essential that a class have some means of disengaging from some fights without dying.  With no means to disengage a class becomes useless in solo pvp not least because of the 2-4 member gang bang squads that are so prevelent.<br><br>Now that I think of it this position may only be valid on rallos zek and only because of item loot.  On teams servers the difference between forcing someone to leave the zone in defeat and killing them would be a lot smaller, the fact that rogues have a difficult time finishing off non poisoned oponents (or at least I do) would be less meaningful,  and death to a group of 4 wizards would be less meaningful but for those of us on rallos zek who wont go around fully bagged anticipating defeat ,it is.<br><br>It also occurs to me that perhaps i haven't explained this as well as I could have and perhaps you who read this see this as a defense of cowardice but until you have had to play in an environment where you have to fight again and again when a single defeat means the loss of something expensive and or hard to replace and at the same time watch countless casters shadowstep run or gate away even at very low hp I don't think you'll get it.<br><br>Do NOT nerf melee gate )). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwolandgrauensturm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Woland Grauensturm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/2/01 4:59:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> <br>I find it ridiculous when melee players complain about PvP. At least on Vallon Zek, they dominate the high level gameplay. I was doing well pet kiting a level 60 paladin yesterday with my 56 necro pet that had MR buff (so it resisted or broke most roots), well, except that the pet took heavy damage from the coldain ring dmg shield, and that pally eventually turned to pet and smacked it with a few hits from his epic. Note - pally fled eventually, which isn't very common.<br><br><br><br>No, the big problem in PvP is the huge advantage that hybrids and melee's have towards casters and priests. Given how PvP works on the coin only servers, it is a joke that spell damage and pet damage is reduced to 66%, while melee damage, damage shields and archery, does 100% damage. <br><br>All sorts of damage should have the same reduction. That would be a huge improvement for PvP balance.<br><br><br>I do agree with some points on the list though, like bards poofing pets, and line of sight abusing.<br><br> <p><BR><p align="center"><img border="0" src="http://hem.passagen.se/stigard/eqpics/Zarloth_tagline.jpg" width="420" height="150"></p><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/2/01 10:14:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> The lvl 60 game isn't the entire game.  Nerfing all melee dmg down to 2/3 at all lvls would be horrible for the melees and hybrids.  As far as pvp being dominated completely by hybrids and melees in the high lvl game I just don't see it.  Maybe because I'm 54 and it really changes at high 50s and 60, maybe because melees can't wear as much droppable armor all the time on rallos, but I just don't see it.<br><br>The only unbalancing factor in melees favor at lower lvls is the gear available to twinks and you clearly can't balance the game with twinks in mind without screwing over the people who aren't twinks.  Now if we could just get some lvl restrictions on items so lvl 20s couldn't wield a trak tooth or a blood point...<br><br>Personally my view is if your a necro and you think rogues are overpowered in pvp you are lacking in skills.<br><br>pyrocruor 2000 dmg dmg dot<br>Cessation 1000dmg debuff dot<br>vex 1100 lifetap over time.<br>Ebolt 1100 poison dot<br>Deflux 310 lifetap 3 second cast<br>DMF +70 pr and levitate<br>Scent of Terris fr dr and pr down by 50 in pvp<br>Splurt 1800 dmg dot<br><br>Here are a few tips...<br><br>Know who your enemies are.<br><br>Watch your zone list for enemies.<br><br>When a known enemy apears in the list use your pet to target him as described above.<br><br>Never hunt at a zone line.<br><br>Try never to hunt anywhere easily accessable to someone at the zone line.<br><br>In a dungeon where the rogue is sneaking through since you can target him from anywhere you can test to see if hes in range from time to time.<br><br>You may want to make a hotkey that goes like...<br>/pet attack name<br>/pet back off<br>/target name of your current pet<br>/assist<br><br>Then hit it from time to time and try to cast.  If your enemy is sneaking around in a dungeon to reach you he will probably agro a mob when your spell breaks his hide in any high lvl dungeon he will most likely die.<br><br>If no mobs are around or its outdoors he should have your pet on him and dots that he wont be able to dispell without prenerf pumice.<br><br>Even if it doesn't go like this you can shadowstep and work the terain in order to keep from dying to his dmg and meanwhile even if you can't cast much you should be able to get some defluxes off while your pet works on killing the rogue.<br><br>If you get a good shadowstep off you should easily be able to even cast a dot that he wont be able to get rid of without ditching your pet.  Of course the rogue could potentially manage to finish you off (hint try not to show your back)<br><br>Heres another idea shaman dmg shield potion + banshee aura thats a 43 dmg shield at 60<br><br>The rogue is surely not helpless but to describe melees as needing a nerf to 2/3 dmg is ridiculous.<br><br>Strategies for the rogue include dragging the pet off , killing it, then healing up with a velious bp.<br>Rooting the pet with nets farmed in velious.<br>If the necro is inclined to cast a lot of pumiable dots and doesn't have a pet up let em then step out of range and pumice em off using up their manna. (yes this requires a dumb necro)<br>Fighting repeatedly then backing off and healing with mrylo or velious bp<br>Suprising the necro and wrecking him.<br>Catching him indoors supposing he doesn't start casting before you come into sight via the pet target thing.<br>Luring him into somewhere shadowstep wont take you very far and hurting him.<br>Pre nerf pumice if you've got it.<br>Training the pet on some npc that hates necros (ok this is kinda cheap)<br>Running past agro npcs but sneaking letting them run straight to you visible and agro.  The pet will get killed by the mob and the necro will take some dmg before fding or trying to gate.  If you don't want to cause them exp death you can let them gate or fd...or not.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utetriancorbec.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tetrian corbec</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://faceweb-004.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/61/2161961.bmp" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/22/01 6:59:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> [quote] Pet kiting. This is where a pet class runs around in a circle with their pet on a melee who can't hit back because of the melee range bug. This is extremely lame since the melee has no chance ot hit back.[/quote]<br><br>Explain to me, how is a mage for example, going to kill a rogue - without the ability to kite you with his pet? you can kill him in close to one backstab, or in a few attack rounds, he cant channel spells through dual