ack full of potions, cure disease, sow, levi, EB, cure poison.<br><br>So basicly you are saying that chanters should not have the ability to PK solo but you're upset because melee's should? If melees grouped up with a caster you would not be having problems with levi, melee range bug (casters can root, snare or cripple), DS's, and los exploiting (since casters can root them). <br><br>One of the best PK's I know is a solo rogue btw. I guess he learned how to work around all these &quot;bugs&quot;. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/25/01 5:22:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> The design defects are not so extreme that its impossible to get kills...doesn't mean its good design though. <br><br>Requiring los would mean you really couldn't fight in very tight coridors but the solution to that is...don't fight in very tight coridors in fact as a caster I'm sure you allready know this isn't the best place for you to fight (in fact Id go so far as to say the only way you could fight in this situation is to cheat and cast through a wall where you couldn't be seen or attacked back) and as a pvper Id expect you to know that choosing where and when to fight means a lot.  <br><br>Original statement -rogues have almost 3k <br>Next statement     -rogues 5 lvls higher than me have 2.2k<br><br>Still trying to exagerate matters to prove your point <br><br>As far as hp totals compare the same lvl chars please...<br><br>54 rogue 1600hp<br>54 enc 1100hp +640 rune = 1740 dmg absorption <br><br>You might try rune 5 + dmg shield potion (27dmg at your lvl) + feedback (11ds) +fire elemental form (14ds at your lvl) for a total of a 52 dmg shield.  Hell if this doesn't allready hurt them enough you could mez them and recast rune.<br><br>You could also try levitating overhead with a pet on them.  A point about lev, even if I'm leved as a rogue I have a hell of a time actually hitting someone who is flying and if they happen to have lev well you could always dispell em.<br><br>You could try not turning your back on a rogue.<br><br>You could use a charmed pet (dangerous I know) In some cases you could mez, lower their str to nil THEN charm something or use an allready charmed mob to finish them.<br><br>BTW pointing out design flaws or some legitimate pvp strategies as I did above isn't meaning to say rogues suck they don't. As far as your friend there well guess what an awesome pvper is probably going to rock no matter what class he or she plays but that doesn't mean that rogues as a class should have to deal with every gimp caster using what is to me an obviously exploitive strategy.<br><br>I pointed out a few strategies that don't require you to be &quot;too close&quot; to a melee unless too close is anywhere they can see you and attack you back lol which personally is what I think your saying.<br><br>Considering the feedback I would be quite happy if the following changes were made...<br><br>-Line of sight required on all nukes debuffs and dots.<br>-Charm no longer poofed pets.<br>-Pumice casting time was lowered somewhat or a new pumice was added that doesn't proc till 50 with a lower casting time.  If you did this you could dispose of golem wands they are kinda unbalancing in some cases.<br>-The pet attack assist trick was nerfed and /invite playername was a command usable zone wide to make Coth possible.<br>-Ghosting was adressed in some fashion<br>-The position of a player you have targeted relative to you should be calculated more precisely and checked more often so that players could hit eachother more easily with melee attacks.<br><br><br>Requests removed for shaman ds and levitate changes.<br><br>I think that all of these requests would lead to more interesting and more balanced gameplay. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/25/01 7:26:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> Forgot to adress this bs here.<br><br>&quot;Explain to me, how is a mage for example, going to kill a rogue - without the ability to kite you with his pet? you can kill him in close to one backstab, or in a few attack rounds, he cant channel spells through dual wield, and all his spells only does 66percent of their damage against you, not counting your ressists.  No thats right, he cant.&quot;<br><br>You can't channel scars of sigil a 2 second spell? /boggle<br><br>A kill with one double backstab doesn't occur till lvl 59 with duelist disc and even so... if you see a rogue go duelist BACKUP for the 9 seconds till it wears off!<br><br>Your pet should play a role in the fight but the run around till your pet beats the rogue down because the melee range bug prevents him from hitting you is just damn lame.  Its a gimp tactic.<br><br>Bet the idea that your pet would do reduced dmg vs a moving target made your blood boil.  You think thats how melees feel?  You wanna suggest a different solution to keep people from using the above gimp tactic than either of the 2 ideas I presented? Go ahead.<br><br>I suppose you could let us evade the pet. Say the pet lose the ability to autofollow for 5 seconds(evade is usable every 10 seconds and doesn't always work)  Make the ability fail if the rogue remains in the same area right after evading.  Meaning if the mage is moving around trying to cast the pet attacks for 100% of the time.  If the mage is just fleeing with the pet attacking the pet wont be able to do near as much dmg. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A> at: 11/25/01 7:47:28 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urhainy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhainy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 7:24:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> My main point about the line of sight thing is that if they did change it, it would way to easy to exploit by melees AND casters. In my oppion the only way you should be able to avoid getting hit once that wizzy begins casting is if you interupt him. NOT if you dive into the water or run around the corner. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/26/01 7:43:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Broken or poorly designed aspects and strategies in pvp</span><hr size=1> So you prefer it set up in such a way that only you can exploit it in other words?<br><br>Melees using it to escape is less important than casters exploiting it to get kills.<br><br>As I said before if he goes around a corner follow him.  If you lose track of him and can't find him to nuke well your basicly in the same position the melee is in if he loses track of you.  Whats unfair about that?<br><br>Interesting pvp is where both parties have to think about where and what their opponent is doing.  Not try to lose him so you can get some cheesy hits off from behind a wall. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uurshulgi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Urshulgi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 4:18:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> pointless to argue with you</span><hr size=1> I'm not going to post any more responses to your whines about how all casters are exploiters.<br><br>Yes I can often channel Scars of Sigil and do 200 dmg if I'm super lucky and his resists suck. <br>Do you know how much damage a rogue can do in that short period of time that he's in melee range? Doesn't backstab have close to a 120degree arc in which it works?  <br><br>Tell you what guy, how about a level 60 caster and a level 60 melee switch characters for a day and see which one is whining when they are done.  As a rogue you could just camp the bank in thurgadin all day and rack up massive kills on those poor bastards.  If you pvp as a legit caster and don't use los I guarantee you would no longer dismiss casters complaints about high level pvp.<br><br>At least you aren't alone in your opinions that melees should be gods in pvp, you have plenty of support from the jerry's kids that verant pays to develop their game. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=518.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=518.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=518.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showMessageRange?topicID=518.topic&start=81&stop=81>5</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showPrevMessage?topicID=518.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showNextMessage?topicID=518.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=518.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.emailToFriend?topicID=518.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.threadControl?topicID=518.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=518.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=518.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> 